reason: I need to see the full height of the building to estimate it, so I will start by looking up to find the roof.
My heading was reset after looking up, so I need to rotate back to face the building at approximately 267° West before I can continue assessing its height.
I have reoriented myself to face the building; now I will look up again to see the top and estimate its height.
The system reset my heading again; I need to reorient to 267° West and look up at the same time to see the top of the building.
